1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,200
Science has a clearer story about airborne vs droplet than social media does.

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:09,600
Airborne transmission involves tiny particles lingering in the air for hours.

3
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:10,800
Think of aerosols.

4
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:17,200
Droplet transmission, on the other hand, is larger, heavier droplets that fall quickly—think sneezes and coughs.

5
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:23,200
Studies show airborne viruses can travel distances over 6 feet, while droplets typically travel less.

6
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:27,600
Understanding this helps us make better choices about masks and ventilation.

7
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:28,400
Stay informed!

8
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:31,200
Like and follow for more science insights.
